4:
Heard Kweggwe lands are a lot
calmer now. Or so my cousin says.
7:
Is that so... The reconstruction efforts
in Oxtan territories are lagging
behind as expected. Should we
increase support?
10:
I doubt they'd accept the help. We
need some kind of pretext.
12:
Hey slackers, what're you doin'
loitering in front of my place?
15:
It's a convenient location to gather.
You've set up shop on prime real
estate, Will.
18:
Too bad! You're getting in the way of
my business. Off with ya!
20:
C'mon, Will! We're old friends, ain't
we? Cut us some slack!
22:
Quiet, you! I'm just a merchant now!
One that does a good deal of
business with the Swallow
Knightsâ€”for which I'm thankful!
24:
But you guys and your endless
schemes and spying... You sure
you're gonna be all right?
27:
For now. We're still in the
information-gathering phase.
29:
I figure if we collect intelligence from
both the Farlands and Palpebra,
we're more likely to find something
useful.
32:
I think we're about done here. Thank
you for your reports, everyone.
35: Captain! Mind if I join you?
38:
I'm grateful for the offer, but I have
plans with His Highness.
40:
When I invited you to our order, I did
not intend for it to consume your
entire life. Please, go about your
days as you did before.
43:
Persistent, aren't you? How long
have you nursed that crush?
53:
What were you thinkin', bringin' His
Highness somewhere so
dangerous?!
58:
It's your fault for being so hard to
track down. You even gave us the
slip in Starview Village, of all places.
61:
We need to talk...
About the assassination.
65:
Ugh, so now yer another
pain-in-my-ass politician, huh?
They're the worst.
68:
What've we got here? Information
from the Guild?
72:
I've been speaking with people who
were around when it happened. It's
mostly gossip and rumors, truth be
told.
74:
But now that we know, we must act.
We can't sit idly by.
78:
Don't even think about it. This is the
kinda thing you should leave to me.
80:
Ya don't wanna risk losing any
friends.
84:
And you don't consider yourself to
be one of my friends?
87:
Someone out there has corrupted
the light and disrupted many lives.
91:
I must find out why, and how. That
much is not up for debate.
95:
Everyone here is aware of that, and
has lent me their aid in the matter.
97:
Even if you didn't see this through to
the end, we still would.
99:
We may be waltzing directly into
danger. Would you be able to sit by
and let that happen, Vyron?
104:
...Ugh, yer WORSE than a politician.
Smooth-talkin' son of a...
107:
I was already thinkin' about sharing
my intel, things being what they are.
I just wasn't sure who to share it with.
109:
If yer so dead-set on doing this,
maybe it'd serve ya well.
120:
But don't go thinkin' I'll always be
around to save your ass. You've
gotta clean up yer own messes.
122: Guess I'm not one to talk though, eh?
134:
You look like your soul's left your
body. Has our great captain spent
all of his energy?
138:
Even now, as we speak, I'm putting
my friends in danger. That thought
alone is enough to drain my spirits
and leave me exhausted.
140:
I'm convinced that, at the moment,
House Kwetur lacks the resources to
reach us. And yet...
145:
And yet you choose to bear that
mental burden.
149:
I once thought about staying on my
own path and keeping to what was
within my abilities, but it seems I'm
not so easily satisfied.
152:
But it's thanks to all of you that I was
able to take the first step.
156:
Is that so? In my view, you've never
lost sight of the light. Not for a single
moment.
159:
As you say, you've never been one
to give up.
167:
I know very well how determined
you are. For one, how many times
was I forced to eat one of your failed
attempts at cooking?
171:
Ah... You, er, have my sincerest
apologies for that.
174:
Still. I owe my growth to youâ€”all of
you.
176:
Coming to Starview allowed me to
re-examine who I was. It served as a
reminder of the sheer vastness of
our world.
180:
Even my blade owes its power to
another world. It was only thanks to
it that I was able to even imitate the
Nouin style of swordsmanship.
184:
That other world being Qualia City, if
I recall? I bet Alk was quite jealous.
188:
Come now, Light. Idle gossip like that
doesn't befit the great Champion.
192:
Regardless, I'm prepared to wield
this sword whenever it is needed. Of
course, that includes the coming
battles those two face.
196:
I never doubted your resolve for a
second. We're all counting on you.
202:
Who knows. It's not like I'm his
personal guard. Still... I suppose I
can't completely disregard him.
204:
His Highness exceeds me in most
regards. I am no more than a man
who tried to forge a pathâ€”only to
get bogged down in a quagmire
along the way.
206:
But still, as a leader, I think I have
something to offer.
212:
...You know, you remind me a great
deal of myself.
216:
Is that so?
I'm honored to hear that.
219:
I don't have to choose one or the
other. I can do bothâ€”because I want
to.
221:
That's what being a free knight
means, after all.
